00:13:17,720 --> 00:13:20,280
You know you're workin'
with a genius?

241
00:13:20,360 --> 00:13:23,511
We're all smart,
but he wears glasses.

242
00:13:23,600 --> 00:13:24,749
Yeah.

243
00:13:24,840 --> 00:13:27,673
W-what's good? Pine, right?

244
00:13:27,760 --> 00:13:30,877
Oak, redwood. Redwood is what
woodpeckers peck on.

245
00:13:30,960 --> 00:13:33,269
It's supposed to be the strongest.

246
00:13:33,360 --> 00:13:35,271
- Good trees, right?
- Yeah.

247
00:13:35,360 --> 00:13:38,477
- This looks good.
- Whoa, look how long it is.

248
00:13:38,560 --> 00:13:40,039
We could build a house.

249
00:13:40,120 --> 00:13:43,237
- We're just building a tunnel.
- Whoa.

250
00:13:43,320 --> 00:13:45,550
- Or, like, a house.
- Yeah.

251
00:13:45,640 --> 00:13:47,596
(Ray ) How much is that?

252
00:13:47,680 --> 00:13:50,240
- 1,000 bucks.
- 1,000 bucks a box? Jesus!

253
00:13:50,320 --> 00:13:52,754
- How many sticks in a box?
- 50.

254
00:13:52,840 --> 00:13:57,960
My God, this is...this is
robbery. This is unbelievable.

255
00:13:58,040 --> 00:14:00,349
What do we need this dynamite for?

256
00:14:00,440 --> 00:14:02,795
What? Just be careful...

257
00:14:17,640 --> 00:14:19,596
I don't like the colour...

258
00:14:20,720 --> 00:14:22,153
Ohh, phew!

259
00:14:22,240 --> 00:14:24,231
Can I have one of these?

260
00:14:24,320 --> 00:14:25,639
Uh, OK.

261
00:14:25,720 --> 00:14:27,472
- One of these?
- Mm-hm.

262
00:14:27,560 --> 00:14:29,949
- OK, you want a bag?
- No, that's OK.

263
00:14:30,040 --> 00:14:33,237
I haven't got a bag.
You'll take 'em like this?

264
00:14:34,080 --> 00:14:35,308
(Ray ) It's a lot of work,

265
00:14:35,400 --> 00:14:38,995
but when it's over we're all
gonna be well compensated.

266
00:14:39,080 --> 00:14:41,435
Who's gonna work the drill?.

267
00:14:41,520 --> 00:14:44,796
- What do you mean?
- I don't know how to.

268
00:14:44,880 --> 00:14:47,030
There's nothing to that.

269
00:14:47,120 --> 00:14:51,432
Whoever's working it, I tell ya,
it's gonna make a lot of noise.

270
00:14:51,520 --> 00:14:54,080
No, no, hey,
what do you think this is?

271
00:14:54,160 --> 00:14:56,833
We wrap this blanket around it,
it's fine.

272
00:14:56,920 --> 00:14:59,434
No, no, you gotta know
how to work that.

273
00:15:01,280 --> 00:15:03,794
(Tommy ) Whoa! Shut it off!

274
00:15:03,880 --> 00:15:06,394
(Shouting and drilling)

275
00:15:07,880 --> 00:15:11,190
Guys, shut up! What did you do?!

276
00:15:11,280 --> 00:15:14,431
- We ain't started yet.
- What are you waitin' for,

277
00:15:14,520 --> 00:15:15,839
the drilling season?

278
00:15:15,920 --> 00:15:18,878
Do me a favour,
go upstairs and bake, will ya?

279
00:15:18,960 --> 00:15:22,157
You know,
I-I don't need any help.

280
00:15:22,240 --> 00:15:25,073
(Denny ) Got it?
(Ray ) You better brace me.

281
00:15:28,240 --> 00:15:31,550
You said you were fine!
What are you doing?!

282
00:15:36,160 --> 00:15:38,469
Get that thing! Get that thing!

283
00:15:38,560 --> 00:15:41,154
- Got it?!
- Yeah, I got it!

284
00:15:41,240 --> 00:15:42,719
I can't hold it!

285
00:15:45,160 --> 00:15:47,151
(All shouting and screaming)

286
00:15:48,960 --> 00:15:53,078
I'm gettin' out of here!
I can hear somebody in the store!

287
00:15:54,640 --> 00:15:58,155
Could we have half a dozen
of the chocolate cinnamon?

288
00:15:58,240 --> 00:15:59,958
We're closed. For Easter.

289
00:16:00,040 --> 00:16:01,792
That was three months ago.

290
00:16:01,880 --> 00:16:04,519
- Greek Easter.
- That was two months ago.

291
00:16:04,600 --> 00:16:05,919
Chinese Easter!

292
00:16:06,000 --> 00:16:08,230
I'd like a cookie for my daughter.

293
00:16:08,320 --> 00:16:10,390
- Honey, what kind?
- All right!

294
00:16:10,480 --> 00:16:13,233
Have a cookie.
Yeah, sure, take a cookie.

295
00:16:13,320 --> 00:16:15,754
- How you doing?
- Oh...hi!

296
00:16:15,840 --> 00:16:18,479
- You still open?
- Yeah, yeah, sure.

297
00:16:18,560 --> 00:16:21,996
- Two cherry cinnamon.
- Cherry cinnamon, right.

298
00:16:22,080 --> 00:16:24,469
- New here, huh?
- Just opened today.

299
00:16:24,560 --> 00:16:25,675
(Banging)

300
00:16:25,760 --> 00:16:27,193
What's all that noise?

301
00:16:27,280 --> 00:16:30,113
That's...the cookie press.
It needs oil.

302
00:16:30,200 --> 00:16:33,397
There's...
a slight leak...downstairs.

303
00:16:33,480 --> 00:16:36,278
- This is the plumber.
- There's a tiny leak.

304
00:16:36,360 --> 00:16:38,920
- What do I owe you?
- Oh, no charge.

305
00:16:39,000 --> 00:16:42,515
- Thanks a lot. Take it easy.
- I gotta get some sandbags!

306
00:16:42,600 --> 00:16:45,194
Oh, the cookies are 85 cents for...

307
00:16:45,280 --> 00:16:48,795
- Get the sandbags!
- Relax, you're a perfect fit!

308
00:16:48,880 --> 00:16:51,553
- Where are the sandbags?!
- Just relax!

309
00:16:53,960 --> 00:16:56,190
OK, so we got off to a shaky start.

310
00:16:56,280 --> 00:16:58,430
Yeah, I'd say it was shaky, yeah.

311
00:16:58,520 --> 00:17:01,717
Frenchy, there's gonna
be glitches, so what?

312
00:17:01,800 --> 00:17:03,995
Tomorrow I'll bring a bathing suit.

313
00:17:04,080 --> 00:17:07,595
I'm not discouraged,
cos I don't get discouraged.

314
00:17:07,680 --> 00:17:11,878
There was a woman on before,
she's got 200 pairs of shoes.

315
00:17:11,960 --> 00:17:14,793
You'll get yours Frenchy,
I promise you.

316
00:17:14,880 --> 00:17:17,678
This time in a month or two
we'll be in Miami,

317
00:17:17,760 --> 00:17:19,273
it'll be great.

318
00:17:19,360 --> 00:17:22,397
"A patron of the arts",
don't that sound great?

319
00:17:22,480 --> 00:17:25,233
- Frenchy...
- Opening night at the opera.

320
00:17:25,320 --> 00:17:27,470
I love you, Frenchy, you know why?

321
00:17:27,560 --> 00:17:29,710
Because you back me all the time.

322
00:17:29,800 --> 00:17:32,633
You know when I first knew
I loved you?

323
00:17:32,720 --> 00:17:35,359
This was a long time ago
if you remember.

324
00:17:35,440 --> 00:17:38,079
Remember I taught you
how to open a safe

325
00:17:38,160 --> 00:17:41,038
by listening to the tumblers,
and you got it.

326
00:17:41,120 --> 00:17:44,317
- That's when I knew.
- You're a very romantic man,

327
00:17:44,400 --> 00:17:47,358
and I'm very lucky because
not many wives get to see

328
00:17:47,440 --> 00:17:50,273
their husbands battling
a ruptured water main.

329
00:17:50,360 --> 00:17:52,794
- I'm crazy about you.
- I'm crazy about you.

330
00:17:54,560 --> 00:17:57,233
- Here, Benny.
- Benny, put it in the bag.

331
00:17:57,320 --> 00:18:00,073
- You... I'll...
- He puts it in the bag.

332
00:18:00,160 --> 00:18:02,594
- This is efficiency.
- Hurry up!

333
00:18:02,680 --> 00:18:05,592
What... Why are you putting
it in his shovel?.

334
00:18:05,680 --> 00:18:08,399
- He puts it in.
- It's called efficiency.

335
00:18:08,480 --> 00:18:10,869
It saves energy.

336
00:18:10,960 --> 00:18:12,598
(Customers chatting)

337
00:18:12,680 --> 00:18:15,274
- Chocolate chip, please.
- Here.

338
00:18:15,360 --> 00:18:17,396
Little girl, what do you want?

339
00:18:17,480 --> 00:18:20,472
- Chocolate fudge.
- OK. You can only have two.

340
00:18:20,560 --> 00:18:22,312
What are you stopping for?

341
00:18:22,400 --> 00:18:24,960
Why? I'm trying to figure this out!

342
00:18:25,040 --> 00:18:28,555
According to this,
we're supposed to take a left turn.

343
00:18:28,640 --> 00:18:30,915
That doesn't mean stop! Let's go!

344
00:18:31,000 --> 00:18:34,151
Will you give me a...
What the hell are you doing?

345
00:18:34,240 --> 00:18:36,993
- What?
- You got your hat on backwards.

346
00:18:37,080 --> 00:18:38,479
Yeah, so?

347
00:18:38,560 --> 00:18:41,279
The flashlight goes in the front!

348
00:18:41,360 --> 00:18:43,316
But it looks cooler like this.

349
00:18:43,400 --> 00:18:45,436
What are you, a jerk?

350
00:18:45,520 --> 00:18:48,671
It's a lot more stylish
than that - look at that!

351
00:18:48,760 --> 00:18:51,149
- You think so?
- Yeah, turn it around.

352
00:18:51,240 --> 00:18:54,357
This is chic.
Yeah, look at that. That's cool.

353
00:18:54,440 --> 00:18:56,192
You got a mirror?

354
00:18:56,280 --> 00:19:00,159
No, I don't. That looks good,
I'll show you when we get out.

355
00:19:00,240 --> 00:19:02,037
Can you keep going, please?

356
00:19:02,120 --> 00:19:04,315
I'm trying to figure the map out!

357
00:19:04,400 --> 00:19:06,277
You want two?

358
00:19:06,360 --> 00:19:08,669
OK, OK, everybody hold on.

359
00:19:08,760 --> 00:19:12,435
That's 1.70, that's it.
Thank you very much. Thank you.

360
00:19:12,520 --> 00:19:15,432
OK, here...chocolate chip...

361
00:19:15,520 --> 00:19:17,715
(Tommy ) What you
gonna do with your share?

362
00:19:17,800 --> 00:19:20,030
How much is my share?

363
00:19:20,120 --> 00:19:23,078
Well, I figure
there's gotta be two million,

364
00:19:23,160 --> 00:19:25,276
I'm counting the jewellery too.

365
00:19:25,360 --> 00:19:29,751
(Benny ) Divided four ways,
that's a half million bucks apiece.

366
00:19:29,840 --> 00:19:32,877
- What about Frenchy?
- She's just a front.

367
00:19:32,960 --> 00:19:34,598
But without her we're dead.

368
00:19:34,680 --> 00:19:36,910
Any broad could sell cookies.

369
00:19:37,000 --> 00:19:40,470
I say she gets a share
but not a full share.

370
00:19:40,560 --> 00:19:42,152
I'd go for that.

371
00:19:42,240 --> 00:19:45,789
What if we each get a fourth
and she gets, like, a third?

372
00:19:45,880 --> 00:19:49,475
- She'd be getting more than us.
- How you figure?

373
00:19:49,560 --> 00:19:52,677
Where you gonna get
four-fourths and a third?

374
00:19:52,760 --> 00:19:55,718
- I don't do fractions.
- Let's not get greedy.

375
00:19:55,800 --> 00:19:59,759
Remember that Bogart movie
where they're digging for gold?

376
00:19:59,840 --> 00:20:03,958
They find the gold and then
this guy turns on his friends.

377
00:20:04,040 --> 00:20:08,113
- Let's not let that happen.
- And he's killed by Hispanics.

378
00:20:08,200 --> 00:20:10,839
- The Treasure Of...
- Treasure Island.

379
00:20:10,920 --> 00:20:14,435
- Right! That was a good movie.
- The best.

380
00:20:14,520 --> 00:20:17,910
OK, folks, here's the deal.
I'm out of cookies, OK?

381
00:20:18,000 --> 00:20:19,797
(Crowd groans )

382
00:20:19,880 --> 00:20:22,189
It's gonna be another two minutes.

383
00:20:22,280 --> 00:20:24,714
That's the way the cookie crumbles.

384
00:20:24,800 --> 00:20:28,395
I've got one cookie left, you
know who's gonna eat this? Me.

385
00:20:29,280 --> 00:20:31,475
(Frenchy ) I gotta put on help.

386
00:20:31,560 --> 00:20:32,879
Help?

387
00:20:32,960 --> 00:20:35,235
Yeah, I can't handle the volume.

388
00:20:35,320 --> 00:20:37,390
What...? A second person?

389
00:20:37,480 --> 00:20:40,870
I can't help it, Ray,
the cookies are selling.

390
00:20:40,960 --> 00:20:45,875
Gee, I never counted on that.
You gotta manage it somehow.

391
00:20:45,960 --> 00:20:49,236
What about my cousin May?
We can trust her.

392
00:20:49,320 --> 00:20:53,393
May's a dodo,
I bring a dodo into a master plan?

393
00:20:53,480 --> 00:20:57,234
- She's not a sQuealer.
- But we'd have to cut her in.

394
00:20:57,320 --> 00:21:00,232
The pot's getting
smaller and smaller.

395
00:21:00,320 --> 00:21:04,279
Well, I can't cook and sell at
the same time, it's a madhouse,

396
00:21:04,360 --> 00:21:05,873
we'll get caught.

397
00:21:05,960 --> 00:21:08,838
Hey, you know what we could do?

398
00:21:08,920 --> 00:21:13,118
May... We could hire May and
not tell her what we're doing.

399
00:21:13,200 --> 00:21:17,352
And she...she'll never catch on.
She's got, you know, and...

400
00:21:17,440 --> 00:21:20,637
We're making enough
from the cookies to pay her.

401
00:21:20,720 --> 00:21:25,077
Absolutely, she'll never figure
out or catch wise to anything.

402
00:21:25,160 --> 00:21:29,517
If you think Denny's slow,
your cousin May is dumb like a...

403
00:21:29,600 --> 00:21:31,875
like a horse
or a dog or something.

404
00:21:33,040 --> 00:21:35,235
Maybe it's not such a great idea.

405
00:21:35,320 --> 00:21:37,993
No, I think...
I think we could do it.

406
00:21:38,080 --> 00:21:40,514
- Where are we?
- Supposed to be here.

407
00:21:40,600 --> 00:21:42,113
Excuse me!

408
00:21:42,200 --> 00:21:44,919
Where's the sugar?
Frenchy wants sugar.

409
00:21:45,000 --> 00:21:48,993
May, stop bothering us,
we're busy here.

410
00:21:49,080 --> 00:21:51,719
I just don't understand the drilling.

411
00:21:51,800 --> 00:21:55,634
I told you, business is good,
we're expanding.

412
00:21:55,720 --> 00:22:00,919
Yeah, a little tea shop so people
can eat cookies and drink tea.

413
00:22:01,000 --> 00:22:04,310
Where are they gonna
drink the tea, in the tunnel?.

414
00:22:04,400 --> 00:22:07,870
I'd explain it but you gotta
understand engineering.

415
00:22:07,960 --> 00:22:09,473
What's engineering?

416
00:22:09,560 --> 00:22:13,599
May, do me a favour,
I told you, we're expanding.

417
00:22:13,680 --> 00:22:16,353
But there's a nail shop next door.

418
00:22:16,440 --> 00:22:20,228
- We made a deal with them.
- You're expanding into there?

419
00:22:20,320 --> 00:22:21,639
May, get your stuff.

420
00:22:21,720 --> 00:22:24,154
You want the sugar... Take a hike.

421
00:22:24,240 --> 00:22:26,834
Get the sugar and go, we'll call you.

422
00:22:26,920 --> 00:22:29,878
(Tommy ) This broad's big trouble.

423
00:22:29,960 --> 00:22:32,428
Is it safe having that broad around?

424
00:22:32,520 --> 00:22:33,873
She's harmless.

425
00:22:33,960 --> 00:22:36,633
(Benny ) I think
we've made a wrong turn.

426
00:22:36,720 --> 00:22:39,075
Oh, please! Give me the map.

427
00:22:39,160 --> 00:22:42,550
- What're you talkin' about?
- For God's sakes.

428
00:22:42,640 --> 00:22:46,315
This is fine, I don't know
what you're in a dither about.

429
00:22:46,400 --> 00:22:49,631
- You're holding it upside down.
- I am?

430
00:22:49,720 --> 00:22:52,871
You were reading this
upside down all along?

431
00:22:52,960 --> 00:22:54,313
Get off my back.

432
00:22:54,400 --> 00:22:57,551
Can I help it
if they print these things like this?

433
00:22:57,640 --> 00:22:59,756
OK, thank you very much.

434
00:22:59,840 --> 00:23:02,957
I gotta get another plate
of the...cherry...

435
00:23:03,040 --> 00:23:06,271
- Can I help you? Next?
- I'm coming right back.

436
00:23:06,360 --> 00:23:10,114
Can I get two cherry cinnamon?
How you doin'?

437
00:23:10,200 --> 00:23:13,556
We're doin' something right!
Two cherry cinnamon.

438
00:23:13,640 --> 00:23:16,598
- You new here, huh?
- No, this is my first day.

439
00:23:16,680 --> 00:23:19,717
These are the greatest cookies
I ever tasted.

440
00:23:19,800 --> 00:23:23,509
- Oh, really? We're expanding.
- No kidding?

441
00:23:23,600 --> 00:23:26,160
Yeah, some guys are
working right now,

442
00:23:26,240 --> 00:23:29,038
- tunnelling under next door.
- Really?

443
00:23:29,120 --> 00:23:31,111
- Yeah.
- Did you try the fudge?

444
00:23:31,200 --> 00:23:34,556
We were talking about
what a success this place is.

445
00:23:34,640 --> 00:23:37,518
- About the restaurant.
- What restaurant?

446
00:23:37,600 --> 00:23:41,832
You know, the guys in the back
tunnelling under the nail shop?

447
00:23:41,920 --> 00:23:44,753
- What are you talking about?
- The tea room.

448
00:23:44,840 --> 00:23:46,717
May, come here!

449
00:23:46,800 --> 00:23:50,713
We're at the Sunset Bake Shop
where the lines wait patiently

450
00:23:50,800 --> 00:23:53,598
for the most
fabulous cookies in New York.

451
00:23:53,680 --> 00:23:55,272
What's goin' on here?!

452
00:23:55,360 --> 00:23:58,670
And you're the heart
of Sunset Cookies, Miss...?

453
00:23:58,760 --> 00:24:00,318
Frenchy Winkler.

454
00:24:00,400 --> 00:24:03,597
Frances, but everybody
calls me Frenchy.

455
00:24:03,680 --> 00:24:07,958
Standing here, one can inhale
the aroma of chocolate, cinnamon

456
00:24:08,040 --> 00:24:11,271
and a dozen other
mouth-watering taste treats.

457
00:24:11,360 --> 00:24:14,716
Is it true customers wait
half an hour for a cookie?

458
00:24:14,800 --> 00:24:16,518
(Crowd mumble agreement)

459
00:24:16,600 --> 00:24:18,477
That you've rationed sales?

460
00:24:18,560 --> 00:24:21,916
Well, it happened once but...
what's all the fuss?

461
00:24:22,000 --> 00:24:25,072
Where did you learn
the secret of your baking?

462
00:24:25,160 --> 00:24:29,358
It's all I can cook, that and
linguine with turkey meatballs.

463
00:24:29,440 --> 00:24:30,793
(Laughter)

464
00:24:30,880 --> 00:24:32,916
Sir, how is your cookie?

465
00:24:33,000 --> 00:24:36,356
I don't know, it's baked
with nutmeg or something.

466
00:24:36,440 --> 00:24:37,998
But it's great.

467
00:24:38,080 --> 00:24:42,119
And we're expanding, there are
men in the back tunnelling...

468
00:24:42,200 --> 00:24:43,713
No, no, May! Get back!

469
00:24:43,800 --> 00:24:48,669
I can't take this, Frenchy!
We don't want this attention.

470
00:24:48,760 --> 00:24:52,230
I didn't hire a publicity agent,
they just showed up.

471
00:24:52,320 --> 00:24:55,073
I know, but it's putting us
in the toilet!

472
00:24:55,160 --> 00:24:58,994
I can't concentrate,
there's people demanding cookies,

473
00:24:59,080 --> 00:25:02,436
and Denny got bit by a rat,
he needed rabies shots.

474
00:25:02,520 --> 00:25:05,751
- Who, the rat?
- Funny. You should be on TV.

475
00:25:05,840 --> 00:25:07,273
I am! Open your eyes!

476
00:25:07,360 --> 00:25:09,316
Frenchy, I don't like this.

477
00:25:09,400 --> 00:25:13,632
You've been digging for weeks,
when you gonna get somewhere?

478
00:25:13,720 --> 00:25:16,678
It's complicated,
we keep getting lost!

479
00:25:16,760 --> 00:25:19,752
