01:04:27,600 --> 01:04:31,513
Frenchy's out of town, you come
with me, we get the necklace.

1189
01:04:31,600 --> 01:04:34,034
Oh. I never heisted anything before.

1190
01:04:34,120 --> 01:04:38,193
There's nothing to it, I know where
the safe is, I've been planning.

1191
01:04:38,280 --> 01:04:41,636
'I had dinner there one night
and I excused myself,

1192
01:04:41,720 --> 01:04:42,948
'I was very crafty.

1193
01:04:43,040 --> 01:04:45,508
'I went upstairs
and I scoped it all out

1194
01:04:45,600 --> 01:04:49,434
'and found the safe and I got
the whole layout in my mind,

1195
01:04:49,520 --> 01:04:52,239
'so I know we can do this.'

1196
01:05:13,840 --> 01:05:17,674
I don't wanna wind up in jail,
and if this is such a big item

1197
01:05:17,760 --> 01:05:21,469
they'll be turning the town
upside-down looking for it.

1198
01:05:21,560 --> 01:05:24,518
No, I have
a particularly shrewd mentality,

1199
01:05:24,600 --> 01:05:26,716
I got a connection in Chinatown.

1200
01:05:26,800 --> 01:05:29,473
I bring in
a picture of the necklace,

1201
01:05:29,560 --> 01:05:33,678
he makes me an exact duplicate,
I switch, she never knows.

1202
01:05:33,760 --> 01:05:37,514
She's a... Chi Chi's a dumb,
flighty society dame.

1203
01:05:37,600 --> 01:05:41,912
By the time she figures out
there's been a switch,

1204
01:05:42,000 --> 01:05:44,309
I'll be in Florida
or the Cayman Islands.

1205
01:05:45,160 --> 01:05:47,151
(Melancholy classical music)

1206
01:05:57,720 --> 01:05:59,631
(Mobile phone )

1207
01:06:05,000 --> 01:06:07,560
Hello? What?

1208
01:06:07,640 --> 01:06:09,949
- I can't hear you, what?
- Shh.

1209
01:06:10,040 --> 01:06:12,110
I'm in a crypt! I can't!

1210
01:06:12,200 --> 01:06:13,997
What do you mean?

1211
01:06:14,080 --> 01:06:16,833
What are you talking about? How?

1212
01:06:16,920 --> 01:06:18,797
Give me a break, sister, OK?

1213
01:06:18,880 --> 01:06:20,598
- Today?!
- Shh!

1214
01:06:20,680 --> 01:06:24,958
What do you mean
it's an emergency? I...

1215
01:06:32,840 --> 01:06:35,274
- Oh, hi.
- Mrs Winkler?

1216
01:06:35,360 --> 01:06:38,511
We're sorry to bring
you back from your vacation.

1217
01:06:38,600 --> 01:06:41,273
- What's goin' on?
- I've terrible news.

1218
01:06:41,360 --> 01:06:45,399
- Something happened to Ray?
- Sunset Enterprises is bankrupt.

1219
01:06:45,480 --> 01:06:47,596
- How?
- Fraud.

1220
01:06:47,680 --> 01:06:50,911
- Fraud? Who?
- Your accountants.

1221
01:06:51,000 --> 01:06:54,356
I-I-I don't even know
who they are. What?

1222
01:06:54,440 --> 01:06:58,399
- You should have looked.
- We let them handle everything.

1223
01:06:58,480 --> 01:07:01,358
What do I know
about running a corporation?

1224
01:07:01,440 --> 01:07:04,273
Did you ever read
anything you signed?

1225
01:07:04,360 --> 01:07:07,113
No, but they assured us
everything was OK.

1226
01:07:07,200 --> 01:07:09,475
Mrs Winkler, do you want a drink?

1227
01:07:09,560 --> 01:07:13,235
I'd like a 1961 Romanee
Saint-Vivant if we have it.

1228
01:07:13,320 --> 01:07:15,311
I'd have a whisky if I were you.

1229
01:07:15,400 --> 01:07:19,951
Well, I don't understand,
I mean, Sunset's gone?

1230
01:07:20,040 --> 01:07:21,951
Can't we do anything?

1231
01:07:22,040 --> 01:07:26,033
We could put a few people
in jail IF we could find them.

1232
01:07:26,120 --> 01:07:28,759
Oh...this is the worst news.

1233
01:07:28,840 --> 01:07:31,070
Oh, no. No, Mrs Winkler, it's not.

1234
01:07:31,160 --> 01:07:33,037
No? It is to me!

1235
01:07:33,120 --> 01:07:35,475
No, no, the worst news is coming up.

1236
01:07:36,640 --> 01:07:38,756
Oh. All right.

1237
01:07:38,840 --> 01:07:42,913
All right, you better tell me.
Let me sit down.

1238
01:07:43,000 --> 01:07:45,719
They talked about expanding Sunset.

1239
01:07:45,800 --> 01:07:47,791
That's right, yeah.

1240
01:07:47,880 --> 01:07:51,429
To do that you needed a bank
loan, are you aware of that?

1241
01:07:51,520 --> 01:07:53,272
Quite a substantial loan.

1242
01:07:53,360 --> 01:07:54,634
Get to the point.

1243
01:07:54,720 --> 01:07:57,439
You signed a promissory note
to the bank.

1244
01:07:57,520 --> 01:08:01,991
This is exactly what
I've got accountants for.

1245
01:08:02,080 --> 01:08:05,231
Yes, but your accountants
are in Venezuela.

1246
01:08:05,320 --> 01:08:08,437
Wh... This is all so confusing!

1247
01:08:08,520 --> 01:08:12,354
You put up your home and savings
for a monster loan.

1248
01:08:14,680 --> 01:08:16,989
Could you put some cyanide in here?

1249
01:08:17,080 --> 01:08:20,675
- It needs to be stronger.
- You've lost it all, Frenchy.

1250
01:08:20,760 --> 01:08:24,673
Or should I say you've been
swindled out of it all?.

1251
01:08:24,760 --> 01:08:28,435
- You mean I got...
- Nothing. You have nothing.

1252
01:08:28,520 --> 01:08:32,991
No house, no bank account,
just some large, outstanding loans

1253
01:08:33,080 --> 01:08:37,517
which we feel you can best deal
with by filing for bankruptcy.

1254
01:08:37,600 --> 01:08:41,434
Bankruptcy? Bankruptcy?
I'm not up to the "B" words yet.

1255
01:08:41,520 --> 01:08:44,080
- Sorry.
- Does Ray know about this?

1256
01:08:44,160 --> 01:08:47,197
What difference
does it make to Ray? He's gone.

1257
01:09:06,400 --> 01:09:08,994
What did you say?

1258
01:09:09,080 --> 01:09:10,911
(Frenchy ) I'm bankrupt.

1259
01:09:11,000 --> 01:09:15,232
Sunset's gone. Worse,
all my personal dough is gone.

1260
01:09:15,320 --> 01:09:17,276
The whole ride's over.

1261
01:09:17,360 --> 01:09:18,839
Well...

1262
01:09:19,960 --> 01:09:22,394
How could that possibly happen?

1263
01:09:22,480 --> 01:09:24,869
Fraud. My accountants.

1264
01:09:24,960 --> 01:09:29,317
Ray said not to trust them because
the whole firm had moustaches.

1265
01:09:30,960 --> 01:09:33,918
I-I'm gonna get myself
a little Valium.

1266
01:09:34,000 --> 01:09:37,913
David, I can't give you
that loan I promised you.

1267
01:09:38,000 --> 01:09:39,797
What? What did you say?

1268
01:09:39,880 --> 01:09:42,155
It turns out I got people I owe.

1269
01:09:42,240 --> 01:09:44,993
But you did say
I could borrow $400,000.

1270
01:09:45,080 --> 01:09:47,196
I was using it to cement a deal!

1271
01:09:47,280 --> 01:09:52,195
It kills me to cop out on you
like this, but I'm busted.

1272
01:09:52,280 --> 01:09:54,999
- What an idiot.
- I guess I am, yeah.

1273
01:09:55,080 --> 01:09:58,231
H-how could you be
so stupid and irresponsible

1274
01:09:58,320 --> 01:10:02,199
as to allow some patently
cheap and thieving accountants

1275
01:10:02,280 --> 01:10:04,316
to defraud you out of a future?

1276
01:10:04,400 --> 01:10:07,233
How could anyone be that stupid?

1277
01:10:07,320 --> 01:10:09,436
Aren't you a little out of line?

1278
01:10:09,520 --> 01:10:13,035
I've made plans,
I've made commitments to people!

1279
01:10:13,120 --> 01:10:15,156
Oh.

1280
01:10:15,240 --> 01:10:19,233
You got a strange look in your
eye, like the guy from the book.

1281
01:10:19,320 --> 01:10:23,154
Dr Jekyll or Mr Hyde or
Ted Bundy, I can never remember.

1282
01:10:23,240 --> 01:10:27,313
The time I've put in nurturing
an idea that's not gonna happen.

1283
01:10:27,400 --> 01:10:29,755
Is that what it was? The money?

1284
01:10:29,840 --> 01:10:33,071
I-I need my prescription,
my little blue pills

1285
01:10:33,160 --> 01:10:35,151
so I'm gonna...go and get them.

1286
01:10:35,240 --> 01:10:39,677
And I would very much appreciate it
if when I came back you were gone.

1287
01:10:39,760 --> 01:10:41,478
Thank you.

1288
01:10:43,200 --> 01:10:46,875
David, I'd like the cigarette
case back that I gave you.

1289
01:10:46,960 --> 01:10:48,552
I don't think so.

1290
01:10:49,920 --> 01:10:52,115
Wow.

1291
01:10:52,200 --> 01:10:54,873
I asked you for lessons in life.

1292
01:10:54,960 --> 01:10:57,190
I guess I really got one, right?

1293
01:11:04,560 --> 01:11:06,790
(Lively jazz )

1294
01:11:14,440 --> 01:11:17,079
Oh, we're so glad you could come!

1295
01:11:17,160 --> 01:11:18,832
- How are you?
- Good.

1296
01:11:18,920 --> 01:11:24,313
Langston wants to talk to you
about a theatre project in Aspen.

1297
01:11:24,400 --> 01:11:26,755
- Do you ski?
- Me? No, never.

1298
01:11:26,840 --> 01:11:31,311
Do either of you play miniature golf?

1299
01:11:31,400 --> 01:11:33,311
- There's Minky.
- Hello.

1300
01:11:33,400 --> 01:11:37,154
Oh, for heaven's sake! Er... Mingle.

1301
01:11:39,240 --> 01:11:41,435
I don't think you should speak.

1302
01:11:41,520 --> 01:11:44,318
- You said make conversation...
- I know.

1303
01:11:44,400 --> 01:11:46,755
Make conversation but don't speak.

1304
01:11:46,840 --> 01:11:49,195
You know,
don't bring up anything.

1305
01:11:49,280 --> 01:11:52,113
Maybe the weather,
but don't...don't...

1306
01:11:52,200 --> 01:11:55,988
I'm gonna get in the flow
and then kinda glide upstairs.

1307
01:11:56,080 --> 01:11:58,992
- Shall I glide with you?
- No, I'll contact you.

1308
01:11:59,080 --> 01:12:02,709
- Can I get you some champagne?
- Uh...sure.

1309
01:12:18,000 --> 01:12:19,956
(Woman ) Ray!

1310
01:12:22,320 --> 01:12:24,356
I was gonna make a phone call.

1311
01:12:24,440 --> 01:12:26,829
- Have you seen Edgar?
- Edgar?

1312
01:12:26,920 --> 01:12:29,832
Where that man gets off to!

1313
01:12:29,920 --> 01:12:31,911
I was gonna make a phone call...

1314
01:12:32,000 --> 01:12:34,719
- I'll look downstairs.
- Try back there.

1315
01:12:34,800 --> 01:12:36,756
Thank you, Ray.

1316
01:12:51,000 --> 01:12:54,390
(Man ) Oh, Winkler? Do you play golf?

1317
01:12:54,480 --> 01:12:57,552
Golf? No. I was just
gonna make a phone call...

1318
01:12:57,640 --> 01:13:00,677
Guess I was mis...misdirected.

1319
01:13:00,760 --> 01:13:03,149
Yes, I'll just go and use the phone.

1320
01:13:03,240 --> 01:13:06,755
I wanted a match on Sunday
but I'll get somebody else.

1321
01:13:06,840 --> 01:13:08,796
So sorry.

1322
01:14:32,040 --> 01:14:35,635
There'll be rain over
the tri-state area, and fog.

1323
01:14:35,720 --> 01:14:39,269
Temperatures will hover
in the low 60s till Tuesday.

1324
01:14:39,360 --> 01:14:43,672
(Laughs ) I must say,
you are most amusing.

1325
01:14:43,760 --> 01:14:45,318
Would you like a canape?

1326
01:14:45,400 --> 01:14:48,551
Those are shrimp,
these are Quail eggs, and...

1327
01:14:48,640 --> 01:14:50,995
I don't have
any idea what they are.

1328
01:14:51,080 --> 01:14:53,878
Thank you,
I hate things with toothpicks,

1329
01:14:53,960 --> 01:14:55,632
they lodge in your throat.

1330
01:14:55,720 --> 01:14:59,713
(Chuckles ) I'm George Blint,
Mutual Funds, and you?

1331
01:14:59,800 --> 01:15:02,553
May Sloane, I'm a lookout.

1332
01:15:02,640 --> 01:15:05,950
I noticed the way
you walked and carried yourself

1333
01:15:06,040 --> 01:15:07,519
from across the room.

1334
01:15:07,600 --> 01:15:11,229
You remind me
of my wonderful departed wife.

1335
01:15:11,320 --> 01:15:14,437
You can't carry yourself
across the room,

1336
01:15:14,520 --> 01:15:16,590
that's physically impossible.

1337
01:15:16,680 --> 01:15:18,989
(Laughs ) You're charming.

1338
01:15:19,080 --> 01:15:22,277
You're the first woman
I've met since Helen died

1339
01:15:22,360 --> 01:15:23,952
that I could say that about.

1340
01:15:24,040 --> 01:15:26,838
Was Helen your wife
or just a woman who died?

1341
01:15:33,560 --> 01:15:36,518
Where's Mr Winkler?
I wanted to talk to him.

1342
01:15:36,600 --> 01:15:39,672
Oh, he's mingling.
Cloudy today, wasn't it?

1343
01:15:39,760 --> 01:15:43,036
With a chance of light sprinkles
followed by sunshine.

1344
01:15:43,120 --> 01:15:46,715
Absolutely. Chi Chi, would you
get those photos in the bedroom?

1345
01:15:46,800 --> 01:15:49,917
I want to show Mr Winkler
the property in Aspen.

1346
01:15:50,000 --> 01:15:52,673
Yes, I just want to talk
to Dr Henske.

1347
01:15:52,760 --> 01:15:55,399
He'd be perfect
to do Beth Kramer's face

1348
01:15:55,480 --> 01:15:59,553
after the unbelievable job
he did on Mrs Morton's buttocks.

1349
01:15:59,640 --> 01:16:01,710
Oh, I'm going to be right back.

1350
01:16:01,800 --> 01:16:03,756
Would you just...?

1351
01:16:09,720 --> 01:16:11,233
(Door opening)

1352
01:16:16,640 --> 01:16:17,959
Ray...

1353
01:16:18,040 --> 01:16:20,793
Shh! You scared me.

1354
01:16:20,880 --> 01:16:23,758
- For God's sake.
- I came to warn you,

1355
01:16:23,840 --> 01:16:26,559
Mrs Potter's coming
to get some pictures

1356
01:16:26,640 --> 01:16:28,631
that Mr Potter wants you to see.

1357
01:16:28,720 --> 01:16:30,392
She's looking for you.

1358
01:16:30,480 --> 01:16:32,118
Now I've closed the safe.

1359
01:16:32,200 --> 01:16:34,760
It's a tough safe,
I'm out of practice.

1360
01:16:34,840 --> 01:16:38,355
- Did they see you come up here?
- Uh, I don't think so.

1361
01:16:38,440 --> 01:16:41,273
(Sighs ) Get out there
and stand watch.

1362
01:16:41,360 --> 01:16:43,920
I'm gonna do this again.

1363
01:16:44,000 --> 01:16:45,433
Are you OK?

1364
01:16:45,520 --> 01:16:48,512
I'm fine, I'm fine.
Get out, get out!

1365
01:16:48,600 --> 01:16:53,151
If you could fit it in to
your schedule, it would mean so much.

1366
01:16:53,240 --> 01:16:55,674
She's been so down since the divorce

1367
01:16:55,760 --> 01:16:59,673
and don't you think -
he got custody of the Pola-Polas.

1368
01:16:59,760 --> 01:17:03,469
Chi Chi, don't forget those
photographs for Mr Winkler.

1369
01:17:03,560 --> 01:17:04,834
Oh, I'll get them.

1370
01:17:04,920 --> 01:17:06,672
So, you will try?

1371
01:17:06,760 --> 01:17:08,751
- I'll do my best.
- Kiss kiss.

1372
01:17:22,200 --> 01:17:24,156
Mrs Potter is coming!

1373
01:17:34,320 --> 01:17:36,754
(Footsteps fading)

1374
01:17:43,240 --> 01:17:44,559
She's gone.

1375
01:17:44,640 --> 01:17:46,870
- Shh!
- (She's gone.)

1376
01:17:46,960 --> 01:17:48,439
She's gone.

1377
01:17:48,520 --> 01:17:52,718
Mr Winkler wouldn't go without
saying goodbye, would he?

1378
01:17:52,800 --> 01:17:54,791
He's not upstairs.

1379
01:17:54,880 --> 01:17:56,199
Jesus.

1380
01:17:56,280 --> 01:17:58,714
I met a wonderful man downstairs.

1381
01:17:58,800 --> 01:18:00,552
He seemed to like me.

1382
01:18:00,640 --> 01:18:03,598
He said I reminded him
of his wife who's dead,

1383
01:18:03,680 --> 01:18:06,319
but I assume he meant
when she was alive.

1384
01:18:06,400 --> 01:18:10,359
May, can you stop talking
while I'm doing this?

1385
01:18:10,440 --> 01:18:14,718
Little short fella, bright
yellow shirt, unbelievable tie.

1386
01:18:14,800 --> 01:18:19,316
Oh, yes, I know the gentleman,
he was going upstairs before.

1387
01:18:19,400 --> 01:18:23,359
- Are you sure?
- Er, yes, um... Mr Winkler.

1388
01:18:32,040 --> 01:18:33,996
Ray, I hear something.

1389
01:18:36,640 --> 01:18:37,993
- Oh.
- Ooh!

1390
01:18:38,080 --> 01:18:42,358
She's not feeling well.
She had one of her spells.

1391
01:18:42,440 --> 01:18:44,670
- Spells?
- Yes, she gets spells.

1392
01:18:44,760 --> 01:18:47,593
- We have a doctor...
- No, not necessary.

1393
01:18:47,680 --> 01:18:49,591
I-I-I'm a haemophiliac.

1394
01:18:49,680 --> 01:18:53,036
- Dear God, are you bleeding?
- Why would I be bleeding?

1395
01:18:53,120 --> 01:18:54,439
Oh, no, she... Her neck...

1396
01:18:54,520 --> 01:18:57,796
There is, but my nasal passages
are clearing up.

1397
01:18:57,880 --> 01:19:00,348
On weekends
I do this for a hobby.

1398
01:19:00,440 --> 01:19:04,319
- She had champagne, you know...
- Oh, I'll get Dr Henske.

1399
01:19:04,400 --> 01:19:07,631
Really... Ray, you have
my cortisone pills?

1400
01:19:07,720 --> 01:19:09,438
- Me?
- My medication?

1401
01:19:09,520 --> 01:19:13,069
I'll feel better
if Dr Henske looks at her.

1402
01:19:13,160 --> 01:19:16,277
You relax and I'll go get Dr Henske.

1403
01:19:17,760 --> 01:19:21,673
A haemophiliac? Cortisone?
Where do you get this?

1404
01:19:21,760 --> 01:19:24,718
- On TV.
- I said stay with the weather!

1405
01:19:24,800 --> 01:19:27,189
I thought I did
some Quick thinking!

1406
01:19:27,280 --> 01:19:30,033
Yes, and you're going
to be examined now!

1407
01:19:30,120 --> 01:19:31,917
Why? I just had a check-up.

1408
01:19:32,000 --> 01:19:34,753
Jesus, I got no time to work here.

1409
01:19:34,840 --> 01:19:36,671
They'll be back in seconds.

1410
01:19:42,320 --> 01:19:45,118
I can't tell the difference
between these!

1411
01:19:45,200 --> 01:19:47,316
Then you gotta take 'em both.

1412
01:19:47,400 --> 01:19:50,233
I can't, if they
don't find any necklace...

1413
01:19:50,320 --> 01:19:54,359
we've been suspiciously seen
in here, I'll go right to jail!

1414
01:19:54,440 --> 01:19:56,670
Especially with your DNA!

1415
01:19:56,760 --> 01:19:59,433
What has my DNA got to do with it?

1416
01:19:59,520 --> 01:20:03,069
You better choose,
they're gonna be back any minute.

1417
01:20:03,160 --> 01:20:05,116
I ca... I ca...

1418
01:20:16,320 --> 01:20:18,436
Ray, let's go!

1419
01:20:18,520 --> 01:20:20,670
Oh... Grrr!

1420
01:20:24,360 --> 01:20:27,432
All I know
is what I've told you, Doctor.

1421
01:20:27,520 --> 01:20:30,114
She's right in here. Come along.

1422
01:20:30,200 --> 01:20:32,395
Here's Dr Henske!

1423
01:20:32,480 --> 01:20:34,471
What seems to be the trouble?

1424
01:20:34,560 --> 01:20:36,630
False alarm, it was a hot flash.

1425
01:20:36,720 --> 01:20:40,076
I think it was menopausal,
I've seen it before.

1426
01:20:40,160 --> 01:20:42,594
I-I'm given to occasional spells.

1427
01:20:42,680 --> 01:20:45,399
- Spells?
- Not spells, but she...

1428
01:20:45,480 --> 01:20:50,190
No, no! Sometimes for no reason
I get hot and cold flashes

1429
01:20:50,280 --> 01:20:53,955
and the room will spin
and spots will flash before my eyes

1430
01:20:54,040 --> 01:20:56,429
and I'll hear
a ringing in my ears...

1431
01:20:56,520 --> 01:20:58,909
You're making
too much of it, May.

1432
01:20:59,000 --> 01:21:02,754
..and then my tongue turns black
and I can't swallow.

1433
01:21:02,840 --> 01:21:04,114
Really?

1434
01:21:04,200 --> 01:21:06,031
They diagnosed Parkinson's

1435
01:21:06,120 --> 01:21:09,078
but it could be Ebola
or mad cow disease...

1436
01:21:09,160 --> 01:21:12,311
We got to go...
It was a false positive, I think.

1437
01:21:12,400 --> 01:21:14,550
Come on, sweetheart, we're due.

1438
01:21:14,640 --> 01:21:18,155
I do hope you feel better,
and not to worry, Mr Winkler,

1439
01:21:18,240 --> 01:21:20,435
Aspen will have to wait.

1440
01:21:20,520 --> 01:21:23,034
Ebola virus or mad cow?

1441
01:21:23,120 --> 01:21:26,556
I just said the first thing
that came into my mouth.

1442
01:21:26,640 --> 01:21:29,029
- Great.
- Hello, again.

1443
01:21:29,120 --> 01:21:32,157
George. Do I still remind you
of your wife?

1444
01:21:32,240 --> 01:21:35,038
(Laughs ) You kill me, you're great.

1445
01:21:35,120 --> 01:21:38,999
You're not feeling well,
remember? I'm taking her home.

1446
01:21:39,080 --> 01:21:42,470
I'm in the book, May Sloane.
I'll be better.

1447
01:21:42,560 --> 01:21:44,516
Well, I'll call you.

1448
01:21:51,960 --> 01:21:54,554
Ray, I just got the news
about Frenchy.

1449
01:21:54,640 --> 01:21:55,789
Frenchy?

1450
01:21:55,880 --> 01:21:58,440
Didn't you hear? Sunset's gone under.

1451
01:21:58,520 --> 01:22:00,988
She was defrauded out of every penny.

1452
01:22:01,080 --> 01:22:06,074
- I figured you'd know.
- Yeah. No, I do know. I...I...

1453
01:22:08,240 --> 01:22:09,832
(Ray ) Shit.

1454
01:22:19,280 --> 01:22:21,919
(Ray ) I came as soon as I heard.

1455
01:22:23,800 --> 01:22:26,473
I got exactly what I deserved.

1456
01:22:26,560 --> 01:22:28,676
You know, I missed you, Frenchy.

1457
01:22:30,160 --> 01:22:32,435
I'm sorry I blew our cookie company

1458
01:22:32,520 --> 01:22:35,432
but I'm even more sorry
I blew our marriage.

1459
01:22:35,520 --> 01:22:38,830
What are you gonna do?
Everybody makes mistakes.

1460
01:22:38,920 --> 01:22:41,639
The important thing is
I still love you.

1461
01:22:41,720 --> 01:22:44,234
I don't deserve it, I behaved badly.

1462
01:22:44,320 --> 01:22:45,958
You behaved like an ass.

1463
01:22:46,040 --> 01:22:49,635
That's one of those "A" words
you used to practise. Ass.

1464
01:22:49,720 --> 01:22:53,918
But I'm not the easiest guy in
the world. I'm not Mr Sensitive.

1465
01:22:54,000 --> 01:22:56,878
There's things
I coulda done differently.

1466
01:22:56,960 --> 01:23:01,909
We stayed in separate rooms the
whole trip, Ray, that's the truth.

1467
01:23:02,000 --> 01:23:03,991
So where's David now?

1468
01:23:04,080 --> 01:23:06,958
He split the second I went bust.

1469
01:23:07,040 --> 01:23:08,712
No, I don't believe it(!)

1470
01:23:08,800 --> 01:23:11,075
He was hustling me for the dough.

1471
01:23:11,160 --> 01:23:14,516
Jeez. So now we got to
begin again, you know?

1472
01:23:14,600 --> 01:23:16,477
And in more ways than one.

1473
01:23:16,560 --> 01:23:18,755
You still want me?

1474
01:23:18,840 --> 01:23:22,230
Still want you?
You got to ask a Question like that?

1475
01:23:22,320 --> 01:23:25,915
I'm crazy about you.
You're a goddess to me.

1476
01:23:26,000 --> 01:23:29,276
I'm nuts for you.
Of course I want ya.

1477
01:23:29,360 --> 01:23:32,079
But we're broke,
we haven't got a dime.

1478
01:23:32,160 --> 01:23:34,799
We don't own a stick
of this furniture.

1479
01:23:34,880 --> 01:23:38,236
Can I show you something?
May I show you one thing?

1480
01:23:38,320 --> 01:23:40,470
- OK...
- Just let me...

1481
01:23:42,800 --> 01:23:46,076
I think you're gonna be
very, very proud of me.

1482
01:23:47,320 --> 01:23:49,117
That's Chi Chi Potter's!

1483
01:23:49,200 --> 01:23:51,475
Was... Was Chi Chi... Was!

1484
01:23:51,560 --> 01:23:53,516
- Ray!
- Key word, "was".

1485
01:23:53,600 --> 01:23:55,909
- You didn't?!
- I never felt so great.

1486
01:23:56,000 --> 01:23:58,594
I was back in action, I felt alive.

1487
01:23:58,680 --> 01:24:02,195
- Cos I always felt...
- Hey, this is glass.

1488
01:24:02,280 --> 01:24:05,113
What are you talking about?
How's it glass?

1489
01:24:05,200 --> 01:24:08,078
- It's fake.
- What? How would you know?

1490
01:24:08,160 --> 01:24:11,072
I can tell fake,
this ain't even good fake.

1491
01:24:11,160 --> 01:24:13,515
What are you talking about?

1492
01:24:13,600 --> 01:24:17,752
Oh, you know, it might fool some
idiot with no eye and no brains

1493
01:24:17,840 --> 01:24:20,638
but it'd never pass
with a normal person.

1494
01:24:20,720 --> 01:24:25,077
You're saying I got the phoney?
I came away with the wrong thing?

1495
01:24:25,160 --> 01:24:27,037
Sounds like your MO.

1496
01:24:27,120 --> 01:24:29,588
- Nuts! I was in the room...
- Yeah.

1497
01:24:29,680 --> 01:24:34,515
I was gonna substitute the
glass one for the real one...

1498
01:24:34,600 --> 01:24:38,149
It's good to see that you got
the same great instincts.

1499
01:24:38,240 --> 01:24:41,073
You're so wrong...
Can I tell you...?

1500
01:24:41,160 --> 01:24:43,515
- What?
- You take those lessons...

1501
01:24:43,600 --> 01:24:46,194
Wait, I'm gonna show you something.

1502
01:24:46,280 --> 01:24:49,113
..but you know nothing
about jewellery.

1503
01:24:49,200 --> 01:24:52,715
This is... We take this
and fence it, go to Florida...

1504
01:24:52,800 --> 01:24:54,279
It's the goods.

1505
01:24:54,360 --> 01:24:57,750
That won't get us on the subway,
much less to Florida.

1506
01:24:57,840 --> 01:24:59,910
You're such a know-everything.

1507
01:25:00,000 --> 01:25:02,355
You don't have to be
a rocket scientist

1508
01:25:02,440 --> 01:25:04,396
to spot a clinker like this.

1509
01:25:04,480 --> 01:25:06,471
Whoever made it, you overpaid.

1510
01:25:06,560 --> 01:25:08,949
What can I do if you're wrong?
Tell me.

1511
01:25:09,040 --> 01:25:12,430
Can I take your nose
and twist it till you turn blue?

1512
01:25:12,520 --> 01:25:13,953
Sure.

1513
01:25:14,040 --> 01:25:15,439
(Banging)

1514
01:25:23,880 --> 01:25:27,953
Gee... You broke it.

1515
01:25:28,040 --> 01:25:30,031
It's glass, Ray.

1516
01:25:30,120 --> 01:25:33,112
I know, but... Wh... Eh...

1517
01:25:33,200 --> 01:25:34,599
It's, well...

1518
01:25:34,680 --> 01:25:37,069
I'm not cleaning it up!
You broke it!

1519
01:25:37,160 --> 01:25:39,594
You got glass over everything!

1520
01:25:39,680 --> 01:25:42,035
It's dangerous, you...

1521
01:25:42,120 --> 01:25:46,079
Jesus... I don't know what you
see in me, I'm such a screw-up.

1522
01:25:46,160 --> 01:25:48,116
- It's glass!
- Ray...

1523
01:25:48,200 --> 01:25:51,078
All that matters
is that we have each other.

1524
01:25:51,160 --> 01:25:52,878
We didn't there for a while

1525
01:25:52,960 --> 01:25:56,157
and it made me realise
how much I need you.

1526
01:25:56,240 --> 01:25:58,834
But you're married
to a loser, Frenchy.

1527
01:25:58,920 --> 01:26:01,718
No, I'm the luckiest woman
in the world.

1528
01:26:01,800 --> 01:26:03,358
And the brokest.

1529
01:26:03,440 --> 01:26:06,398
We got nothing.
As usual, I come up empty.

1530
01:26:07,480 --> 01:26:08,879
We could pawn this.

1531
01:26:08,960 --> 01:26:12,475
What is this? What is this thing?

1532
01:26:12,560 --> 01:26:13,788
Who...?

1533
01:26:13,880 --> 01:26:16,997
I don't understand,
who's the Duke of Windsor?

1534
01:26:17,080 --> 01:26:18,991
We could probably auction it.

1535
01:26:19,080 --> 01:26:21,594
- Where'd you get this?
- From David.

1536
01:26:21,680 --> 01:26:23,318
David gave you this?

1537
01:26:23,400 --> 01:26:24,958
He doesn't know it yet.

1538
01:26:25,040 --> 01:26:27,235
I don't get it, what do you mean?

1539
01:26:27,320 --> 01:26:31,233
Hey, it was you who taught me
how to open a safe.

1540
01:26:31,320 --> 01:26:36,553
I... That was one of my fondest
memories of our time together.

1541
01:26:36,640 --> 01:26:40,474
What are you saying?
You boosted this from David's safe?

1542
01:26:40,560 --> 01:26:43,597
- Frenchy, that's stealing.
- Not exactly.

1543
01:26:43,680 --> 01:26:46,433
It's a long story, Ray.
Let's sell it.

1544
01:26:46,520 --> 01:26:49,159
I'll fill you in
on the flight to Miami.

1545
01:26:54,920 --> 01:26:57,150
Sweetheart, you...

1546
01:26:58,240 --> 01:26:59,958
are the greatest.

1547
01:27:02,440 --> 01:27:05,671
<i>#</i> Oh, baby,
what I couldn't do

1548
01:27:07,440 --> 01:27:12,514
<i>#</i> With plenty of money
and you, ooh

1549
01:27:12,600 --> 01:27:16,912
<i>#</i> In spite of the worry
that money brings

1550
01:27:17,000 --> 01:27:22,154
<i>#</i> Just a little filthy lucre
buys a lot of things

1551
01:27:22,240 --> 01:27:27,268
<i>#</i> And I could take you
to places you'd like to go

1552
01:27:27,360 --> 01:27:32,229
<i>#</i> But outside of that
I've no use for dough

1553
01:27:32,320 --> 01:27:34,629
<i>#</i> It's the root of all evil

1554
01:27:34,720 --> 01:27:37,280
<i>#</i> Of strife and upheaval

1555
01:27:37,360 --> 01:27:39,351
<i>#</i> But I'm certain, honey

1556
01:27:39,440 --> 01:27:42,477
<i>#</i> That life could be sunny

1557
01:27:42,560 --> 01:27:45,757
<i>#</i> With plenty of money and you <i>#</i>

1558
01:28:56,560 --> 01:28:58,869
<i>#</i> The Champs: "TeQuila"

1559
01:29:46,960 --> 01:29:48,712
<i>#</i> TeQuila <i>#</i>

